  "prompt": "What does mah mean on mobile battery?",
  "response": "\"mAh\" stands for \"milliampere-hours\" and is a measure of electrical charge used to describe the battery capacity of mobile devices like smartphones, tablets, and other portable electronics. It indicates how much electrical charge a battery can store and how long it can power a device before needing to be recharged. A higher mAh rating generally means a longer battery life between charges. For example, a 3000 mAh battery will typically last longer than a 2000 mAh battery under similar usage conditions.",
